REFEREE: 3) Sec 1, Line 1: "almost all massive galaxies (> 10^9 Msun)."\
\
Previous well-established works have defined galaxies with mass < a few 10^9 Msun as "dwarf galaxies" (e.g., Reines & Volonteri 2015) and find a much lower AGN fraction in such systems. While it is possible that most of these galaxies have IMBHs or SMBHs, it is certainly not well-establised that "almost all" have them at this low mass end.\
\
This is quibbling, but it is important to make well-evidenced and well-accepted statements in an introduction, so it is troubling that the very first line of the paper has such a loose and poorly-motivated statement.\
\
