A close reading of the relevant part of the Babyk+ (2019) paper shows that they report at best a marginal correlation. The visual appearance of the correlation in their paper shouldn't be used to judge its strength, because it can be driven by distance-based biases, as noted in that paper. Please restate accordingly. The lack of a strong physical correlation in Babyk+ should also reflect on the statements made in Sec 5.1.2.\
