REFEREE: 6) Sec 2.3.3: "In all the other cases, the ratios are > 1, as typical in AGN-dominated objects."\
\
Whether the emission is "AGN-dominated" or not also depends on the location in the BPT diagrams, which minimally require [N II]/Halpha. A ratio of 1 is well into the star-forming part of the diagram for objects with low [N II]/Ha. Assuming that WISDOM galaxies have a high [N II]/Ha ratio, typical of more massive galaxies, an [O III]/Hb ratio of ~ 1 is in the composite part of the diagram and could be produced by star-formation or a mixture of stellar and AGN emission. It certainly isn't in the "AGN-dominated" part of the diagram, where [O III]/Hbeta ratios are ~ 10.\
\
AUTHORS: We have gathered the [NII]/Halpha ratios as well and produced the BPT diagrams for the 18 galaxies with all the ratios available. We find all but one of these 18 galaxies fall outside the star-forming region. We have included text that details this in Section 2.3.3.\
\
